SIMPLE: noncombatant
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Noncombatant
<hw>Non*com"bat*ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>Any person connected with an army, or within the
lines of an army, who does not make it his business to fight, as any one
of the medical officers and their assistants, chaplains, and others;
also, any of the citizens of a place occupied by an army; also, any one
holding a similar position with respect to the navy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person not attached to a military unit, or not
participating in the military activities of a war; a civilian; <as>as,
the bomb killed twenty <ex>noncombatants</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>noncombinative</ent>⟦br⟧
